Actually - that's the problem with a lot of people, they don't understand how taunt and aggro work.  Warriors have the SAME taunt ability that SK's and Paladins have.  It's their aggro that sucks.<br>
<br>
A lot of warriors think you build aggro by mashing the taunt button - that's not true; in fact you should almost NEVER use taunt in combat (unless your skill isn't maxed) UNLESS you lose control of the mob.<br>
<br>
Taunt does NOT build hate; it only puts you one place higher on the taunt list on a successful taunt.  (so hopefully, if the wizard nukes and gets hate - you can then taunt and pull aggro back to yourself...)<br>
<br>
The problem with it is; it's a 10 second refresh time.  Paladins and Shadow Knights can zap the mob and pull aggro back (via stun or terror) - Warriors have no way to do this, and thus often lose control of the mob...   (especially when the wizard (not picking on any one - just using a nuking class) panics and begins chain nuking to kill the mob to get it off them...)<br>
<br>
But either way, a warrior's taunt is NOT the worst - it's the same as every other classes taunt ability....<br>
<br>
